00:24:02.450 --> 00:24:07.455 align:middle line:90%
Raghu, how can you lose
your cool in court?

00:24:07.455 --> 00:24:12.697 align:middle line:90%
I'm afraid your chances of
magistrate ship may be clouded.

00:24:12.697 --> 00:24:21.469 align:middle line:90%
Chances of a magistrate ship?
That's out of question now.

00:24:21.469 --> 00:24:26.395 align:middle line:90%
Can a lawyer whose wife is under
suspicion ever become a magistrate?

00:24:26.395 --> 00:24:27.554 align:middle line:84%
Raghu!

00:24:27.554 --> 00:24:31.166 align:middle line:90%
The whole town is agog!
- What are you saying?

00:24:31.166 --> 00:24:35.273 align:middle line:90%
Aren't you ashamed to talk like this
about your wife?

00:24:35.273 --> 00:24:38.371 align:middle line:84%
I'm just saying what everyone is saying.

00:24:38.371 --> 00:24:42.352 align:middle line:84%
Let them say what they want.

00:24:42.352 --> 00:24:48.441 align:middle line:84%
You're right. That's what I decided.

00:24:48.441 --> 00:24:51.409 align:middle line:84%
Let them say what they want.

00:24:51.409 --> 00:24:57.743 align:middle line:90%
But how do I get rid of the suspicion?
It's like a leech sucking on...

00:24:57.743 --> 00:25:20.411 align:middle line:90%
some dark corner of my mind!
- What now?

00:25:20.411 --> 00:25:25.374 align:middle line:84%
Nathu! Naina! Bhabhi!

00:25:25.374 --> 00:25:29.482 align:middle line:84%
Where's everyone?

00:25:29.482 --> 00:25:34.406 align:middle line:84%
Send Bhabhi over to me.

00:25:34.406 --> 00:25:38.337 align:middle line:84%
I am scared.

00:25:38.337 --> 00:25:42.228 align:middle line:84%
Why isn't someone coming to me?

00:25:42.228 --> 00:25:50.986 align:middle line:90%
That's my husband.
Please, send him over to me.

00:25:50.986 --> 00:25:54.372 align:middle line:84%
Look Raghu...

00:25:54.372 --> 00:25:57.136 align:middle line:90%
I'm telling you again! That baby
isn't going to be born in this house

00:25:57.136 --> 00:26:00.460 align:middle line:90%
If she wants to have her bastard,
let her go elsewhere.

00:26:00.460 --> 00:26:03.152 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to let the honour
of my family be tainted.

00:26:03.152 --> 00:26:06.128 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to throw this
wanton woman out!

00:26:06.128 --> 00:26:10.383 align:middle line:90%
No! I'm not going anywhere!
No one can take me away from here!

00:26:10.383 --> 00:26:22.618 align:middle line:90%
He knows that I'm innocent!
He trusts me, he trusts me!

00:26:22.618 --> 00:26:26.852 align:middle line:84%
You're here! Now I'm afraid of no one!

00:26:26.852 --> 00:26:30.736 align:middle line:90%
Have you heard?
They want to throw me out!

00:26:30.736 --> 00:26:37.323 align:middle line:90%
They say I'm a wanton woman!
They say, I've no right to be here!

00:26:37.323 --> 00:26:42.406 align:middle line:90%
But now you're here.
No one will dare anymore.

00:26:42.406 --> 00:26:49.667 align:middle line:90%
Tell them I'm untainted!
Tell them you trust me.

00:26:49.667 --> 00:27:12.224 align:middle line:84%
Tell them I'm mothering your child.

00:27:12.224 --> 00:27:16.587 align:middle line:84%
Have you fallen for what they say?

00:27:16.587 --> 00:27:21.868 align:middle line:90%
You're the one who told me...
I don't care for the barking dogs.

00:27:21.868 --> 00:27:28.151 align:middle line:90%
If you desert me, who else
in this world can I turn to?

00:27:28.151 --> 00:27:33.677 align:middle line:84%
Tell me... tell me that you trust me!

00:27:33.677 --> 00:27:35.947 align:middle line:84%
Do you think you're above scrutiny?

00:27:35.947 --> 00:27:54.133 align:middle line:90%
Don't you forget women have
had to stand the test of chastity.

00:27:54.133 --> 00:28:00.654 align:middle line:90%
Why are you quiet?
Speak... speak!

00:28:00.654 --> 00:28:07.224 align:middle line:90%
You can see the state I'm in.
I'm afraid... afraid!

00:28:07.224 --> 00:28:14.102 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to become a mother
...the mother of your child.

00:28:14.102 --> 00:28:20.280 align:middle line:90%
Have mercy! This is your baby.
This baby is yours!

00:28:20.280 --> 00:28:37.748 align:middle line:90%
Get out!
Get out of here!

00:28:37.748 --> 00:28:48.323 align:middle line:84%
"A dutiful wife like Sita."

00:28:48.323 --> 00:28:54.672 align:middle line:84%
"You gave exile to her."

00:28:54.672 --> 00:29:05.735 align:middle line:84%
"Why didn't the earth rip apart?"

00:29:05.735 --> 00:29:11.206 align:middle line:84%
"Why didn't the sky rip apart?"

00:29:11.206 --> 00:29:15.553 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:29:15.553 --> 00:29:20.312 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:29:20.312 --> 00:29:24.682 align:middle line:84%
"The dear one of Lord Ram."

00:29:24.682 --> 00:29:28.104 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:29:28.104 --> 00:29:32.113 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:29:32.113 --> 00:29:36.207 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:29:36.207 --> 00:29:40.788 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:29:40.788 --> 00:29:45.136 align:middle line:84%
"Look, the King of the palace."

00:29:45.136 --> 00:29:48.233 align:middle line:84%
"What a game is he playing!"

00:29:48.233 --> 00:30:03.135 align:middle line:84%
"What a game is he playing!"

00:30:03.135 --> 00:30:07.472 align:middle line:84%
"Look, the King of the palace."

00:30:07.472 --> 00:30:10.556 align:middle line:84%
"What a game is he playing!"

00:30:10.556 --> 00:30:14.470 align:middle line:84%
"What a game is he playing!"

00:30:14.470 --> 00:30:18.768 align:middle line:90%
"From the shell, a pearl,
and in the muck."

00:30:18.768 --> 00:30:22.590 align:middle line:84%
"The beautiful lotus is blossoming."

00:30:22.590 --> 00:30:30.975 align:middle line:84%
"The beautiful lotus is blossoming."

00:30:30.975 --> 00:30:34.331 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:30:34.331 --> 00:30:39.465 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:30:39.465 --> 00:30:42.462 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:30:42.462 --> 00:30:48.382 align:middle line:90%
"Congratulations, Lawyer!
A son has born to you."

00:30:48.382 --> 00:30:55.504 align:middle line:90%
Son of a decent family!
Born in a filthy gutter!

00:30:55.504 --> 00:30:58.497 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:30:58.497 --> 00:31:02.423 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:31:02.423 --> 00:31:06.492 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:31:06.492 --> 00:31:08.480 align:middle line:90%
Do you not know what your wife
and your son went through...

00:31:08.480 --> 00:31:12.266 align:middle line:90%
after you shut your doors on them?
- No

00:31:12.266 --> 00:31:15.402 align:middle line:84%
Nor did you try to find out.

00:31:15.402 --> 00:31:18.499 align:middle line:84%
But I can tell you.

00:31:18.499 --> 00:31:23.610 align:middle line:90%
To get out of your way,
your wife left Lucknow.

00:31:23.610 --> 00:31:29.539 align:middle line:90%
And your innocent son grew up
in a Bombay slum.

00:31:29.539 --> 00:31:40.967 align:middle line:84%
One day...

00:31:40.967 --> 00:31:49.233 align:middle line:84%
Police! Scram!

00:31:49.233 --> 00:31:55.539 align:middle line:84%
Greetings, sir.

00:31:55.539 --> 00:31:59.320 align:middle line:90%
Hey Nathu...
- Hello, Constable.

00:31:59.320 --> 00:32:02.544 align:middle line:90%
What are you up there like a monkey?
Why don't you go to school?

00:32:02.544 --> 00:32:07.174 align:middle line:84%
At school, the master asks for fees.

00:32:07.174 --> 00:32:12.242 align:middle line:90%
My father hasn't the money
to send me to school.

00:32:12.242 --> 00:32:14.710 align:middle line:90%
Look at Leela's son, Raj.
He lives in this slum too.

00:32:14.710 --> 00:32:20.347 align:middle line:90%
His mother is worse off. Yet she
sends her boy to such a big school.

00:32:20.347 --> 00:32:26.980 align:middle line:90%
What did you say? He isn't a boy.
He's a sissy!

00:32:26.980 --> 00:32:32.502 align:middle line:90%
Ma, why do you put oil in my hair?
- Oil keeps the hair soft.

00:32:32.502 --> 00:32:35.266 align:middle line:90%
But why do boys in the
neighbourhood call me sissy?

00:32:35.266 --> 00:32:39.193 align:middle line:90%
So what?
How do they compare with you?

00:32:39.193 --> 00:32:41.903 align:middle line:90%
You're a good boy
who goes to school.

00:32:41.903 --> 00:32:44.452 align:middle line:90%
You'll grow up to become
an educated man.

00:32:44.452 --> 00:32:48.905 align:middle line:84%
And those vagabonds will go to jail.

00:32:48.905 --> 00:32:52.886 align:middle line:84%
Mother, who are called vagabonds?

00:32:52.886 --> 00:32:55.131 align:middle line:84%
The ones who just tramp around.

00:32:55.131 --> 00:32:57.724 align:middle line:90%
Those who think that whatever
belongs to others, belongs to them.

00:32:57.724 --> 00:33:01.857 align:middle line:90%
Those who gamble and drink
instead of going to school.

00:33:01.857 --> 00:33:04.851 align:middle line:84%
And they have fun!

00:33:04.851 --> 00:33:07.558 align:middle line:90%
Ma, when I grow up,
I'll become vagabond too.

00:33:07.558 --> 00:33:14.827 align:middle line:84%
Nonsense! You'll become a lawyer.

00:33:14.827 --> 00:33:17.267 align:middle line:84%
Then a magistrate.

00:33:17.267 --> 00:33:18.843 align:middle line:84%
And then, a judge.

00:33:18.843 --> 00:33:21.264 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

00:33:21.264 --> 00:33:24.349 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

00:33:24.349 --> 00:33:28.964 align:middle line:90%
You're sitting here?
Everyone's out there buying chocolates.

00:33:28.964 --> 00:33:31.716 align:middle line:84%
I don't have money

00:33:31.716 --> 00:33:33.670 align:middle line:90%
Why, doesn't your mother
give you money?

00:33:33.670 --> 00:33:36.754 align:middle line:84%
Daddy gives me a whole Rupee every day!

00:33:36.754 --> 00:33:39.173 align:middle line:84%
You're rich. And I'm poor.

00:33:39.173 --> 00:33:41.926 align:middle line:90%
Eat this
- No.

00:33:41.926 --> 00:33:43.993 align:middle line:90%
Ma says never ask
for anything to eat.

00:33:43.993 --> 00:33:50.613 align:middle line:90%
If she told you not to ask,
go ahead and snatch it.

00:33:50.613 --> 00:33:51.138 align:middle line:84%
Wild!

00:33:51.138 --> 00:33:54.725 align:middle line:90%
Wild?
- No, no, no.

00:33:54.725 --> 00:33:57.381 align:middle line:90%
You're coming to my place
this evening, aren't you?

00:33:57.381 --> 00:34:00.417 align:middle line:90%
Why, what's happening?
- My birthday party!

00:34:00.417 --> 00:34:02.193 align:middle line:84%
You must come! It's going to be fun!

00:34:02.193 --> 00:34:07.190 align:middle line:90%
You know, Daddy has ordered
such a huge cake!

00:34:07.190 --> 00:34:10.687 align:middle line:84%
Happy birthday to you!

00:34:10.687 --> 00:34:20.565 align:middle line:84%
Happy birthday to you!

00:34:20.565 --> 00:34:22.198 align:middle line:84%
Happy birthday to you!

00:34:22.198 --> 00:34:24.448 align:middle line:84%
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

00:34:24.448 --> 00:34:36.914 align:middle line:84%
Let's go and eat ice cream.

00:34:36.914 --> 00:34:41.930 align:middle line:84%
Raj, aren't you giving me a gift?

00:34:41.930 --> 00:34:45.443 align:middle line:90%
I didn't have money to buy anything.
I'll give you some other time.

00:34:45.443 --> 00:34:49.736 align:middle line:90%
Must you only buy something
to make a gift?

00:34:49.736 --> 00:35:00.686 align:middle line:90%
You can give me a flower.
- Really?

00:35:00.686 --> 00:35:03.732 align:middle line:84%
Here you are.

00:35:03.732 --> 00:35:07.101 align:middle line:90%
Someday, I'm going to make
lots of money.

00:35:07.101 --> 00:35:10.791 align:middle line:90%
And I'll buy a gift for you.
Something better than all this.

00:35:10.791 --> 00:35:12.753 align:middle line:84%
Do that.

00:35:12.753 --> 00:35:15.308 align:middle line:90%
But can anything be better
than this flower?

00:35:15.308 --> 00:35:18.810 align:middle line:90%
Ritu! Ritu! Your father
is calling you! - Coming!

00:35:18.810 --> 00:35:28.851 align:middle line:84%
Come on Raj, meet my father.

00:35:28.851 --> 00:35:31.236 align:middle line:84%
You always say this.

00:35:31.236 --> 00:35:33.779 align:middle line:84%
Ritu, say hello to the Judge"

00:35:33.779 --> 00:35:36.263 align:middle line:84%
Hello, Judge.

00:35:36.263 --> 00:35:38.388 align:middle line:84%
Bless you.

00:35:38.388 --> 00:35:44.576 align:middle line:90%
You've grown up in these four years
You must've forgotten me.

00:35:44.576 --> 00:35:46.941 align:middle line:84%
Happy birthday

00:35:46.941 --> 00:35:53.309 align:middle line:90%
I've just arrived from Lucknow.
I owe you a present.

00:35:53.309 --> 00:35:58.777 align:middle line:84%
As of now, I can give you a flower.

00:35:58.777 --> 00:36:05.664 align:middle line:84%
Here you are.

00:36:05.664 --> 00:36:09.395 align:middle line:84%
Let me put it on your hair.

00:36:09.395 --> 00:36:12.681 align:middle line:90%
Someone has already put a flower
over there.

00:36:12.681 --> 00:36:14.690 align:middle line:84%
Raj has given me this flower

00:36:14.690 --> 00:36:18.427 align:middle line:90%
Daddy, this is Raj.
He's in my class.

00:36:18.427 --> 00:36:20.662 align:middle line:90%
I see.
- Hello.

00:36:20.662 --> 00:36:24.430 align:middle line:90%
Hello.
- Hello.

00:36:24.430 --> 00:36:27.503 align:middle line:84%
God bless you, son"

00:36:27.503 --> 00:36:31.924 align:middle line:90%
Raj says that he will become a judge
when he grows up.

00:36:31.924 --> 00:36:34.578 align:middle line:84%
Very good!

00:36:34.578 --> 00:36:38.656 align:middle line:84%
Your father must be a real gentleman.

00:36:38.656 --> 00:36:40.133 align:middle line:84%
What does your father do?

00:36:40.133 --> 00:36:45.665 align:middle line:90%
I don't have my father.
I have only my mother

00:36:45.665 --> 00:36:48.616 align:middle line:90%
Has he passed away?
- No! Don't say that!

00:36:48.616 --> 00:36:54.421 align:middle line:90%
My mother says he is alive.
But...

00:36:54.421 --> 00:36:59.736 align:middle line:90%
He doesn't live with you
...and you haven't seen him either?

00:36:59.736 --> 00:37:03.911 align:middle line:90%
Your father is a strange man.
- Not a word about my father.

00:37:03.911 --> 00:37:07.933 align:middle line:84%
Else... else...

00:37:07.933 --> 00:37:12.982 align:middle line:90%
Raj!
- Rita!

00:37:12.982 --> 00:37:17.910 align:middle line:90%
How can you let your daughter
play with boys like him?

00:37:17.910 --> 00:37:20.273 align:middle line:84%
Go to play, Ritu"

00:37:20.273 --> 00:37:25.362 align:middle line:90%
Why, what's wrong with the boy?
I like him.

00:37:25.362 --> 00:37:30.268 align:middle line:90%
He doesn't even know his father's
name, and you like him?

00:37:30.268 --> 00:37:32.718 align:middle line:90%
I'd say he's just a wastrel
- Forget it.

00:37:32.718 --> 00:37:36.831 align:middle line:90%
Must you hang on to
those rotten old ideas?

00:37:36.831 --> 00:37:39.555 align:middle line:84%
What was the Bandit's name?

00:37:39.555 --> 00:37:41.305 align:middle line:84%
Yes, Jagga.

00:37:41.305 --> 00:37:45.333 align:middle line:90%
I remember you saying the same
at his trial.

00:37:45.333 --> 00:37:49.825 align:middle line:90%
That a bandit's son
always becomes a bandit.

00:37:49.825 --> 00:37:51.449 align:middle line:84%
I still stand by that principle.

00:37:51.449 --> 00:37:56.814 align:middle line:90%
Principles, principles and principles!
It's because of these blind dogmas...

00:37:56.814 --> 00:37:59.757 align:middle line:90%
that you lost someone
as precious as Leela.

00:37:59.757 --> 00:38:02.621 align:middle line:90%
And because of your principles,
you never married again.

00:38:02.621 --> 00:38:05.735 align:middle line:90%
The dry parched desert that
your life is, is your own doing.

00:38:05.735 --> 00:38:07.174 align:middle line:90%
So much so that you would rather
destroy a friendship...

00:38:07.174 --> 00:38:10.315 align:middle line:90%
between two innocent children?
Why, what has the poor child done...

00:38:10.315 --> 00:38:13.947 align:middle line:84%
to bring you to harm?

00:38:13.947 --> 00:38:15.950 align:middle line:84%
Not this boy. But it was...

00:38:15.950 --> 00:38:22.539 align:middle line:90%
someone like him who destroyed my life
...and brought me to disgrace.

00:38:22.539 --> 00:38:25.438 align:middle line:90%
Maybe today, he too says
what this boy just said...

00:38:25.438 --> 00:38:31.454 align:middle line:90%
I'm only my mother's son
...I have no father.

00:38:31.454 --> 00:38:36.484 align:middle line:84%
In every urchin I see him...

00:38:36.484 --> 00:38:39.909 align:middle line:90%
the one whom my wife bore,
the one who isn't mine.

00:38:39.909 --> 00:38:45.323 align:middle line:84%
My wife's, yet not mine.

00:38:45.323 --> 00:38:47.782 align:middle line:90%
Rita looks good in that photo,
doesn't she?

00:38:47.782 --> 00:38:51.533 align:middle line:90%
But Ma, why do you work so hard?
This is why you fall ill.

00:38:51.533 --> 00:38:54.518 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to let you work
anymore, you understand?

00:38:54.518 --> 00:38:58.741 align:middle line:90%
You mad boy! If I don't work,
how are we going to eat?

00:38:58.741 --> 00:39:01.332 align:middle line:90%
I'm a man. I'm the one
who is going to work.

00:39:01.332 --> 00:39:03.566 align:middle line:84%
From tomorrow, no going to school!

00:39:03.566 --> 00:39:07.930 align:middle line:90%
You won't go to school?
Won't you?

00:39:07.930 --> 00:39:10.232 align:middle line:90%
How will you become a gentleman,
unless you educate yourself?

00:39:10.232 --> 00:39:14.825 align:middle line:90%
You want to be a vagabond!
- Mother!

00:39:14.825 --> 00:39:20.208 align:middle line:90%
Without schooling, how can you become
a lawyer, a magistrate, a judge?

00:39:20.208 --> 00:39:28.572 align:middle line:90%
If you say so, I'll go to school
...and I'll work too.

00:39:28.572 --> 00:39:33.454 align:middle line:90%
But I won't become a judge.
At Rita's I met a judge.

00:39:33.454 --> 00:39:57.588 align:middle line:84%
I didn't like him.

00:39:57.588 --> 00:40:05.772 align:middle line:90%
"Go for a stroll, those
who are going."

00:40:05.772 --> 00:40:10.577 align:middle line:90%
"Go for a stroll, those
who are going."

00:40:10.577 --> 00:40:13.929 align:middle line:84%
"Since when we have been waiting,

00:40:13.929 --> 00:40:19.111 align:middle line:84%
we cobblers."

00:40:19.111 --> 00:40:24.357 align:middle line:84%
Page 120.

00:40:24.357 --> 00:40:25.692 align:middle line:84%
Raj.

00:40:25.692 --> 00:40:28.460 align:middle line:90%
Good morning, teacher.
Sorry, I'm late.

00:40:28.460 --> 00:40:32.204 align:middle line:90%
I work, you know. I work
- What's all this?

00:40:32.204 --> 00:40:37.747 align:middle line:84%
Brush, wax... I give you a good polish.

00:40:37.747 --> 00:40:40.870 align:middle line:90%
Your name has been struck
from the rolls.

00:40:40.870 --> 00:40:43.667 align:middle line:90%
What?
- You can't study here anymore.

00:40:43.667 --> 00:40:48.955 align:middle line:90%
But I've brought the fees too! If you
say so, I'll stop polishing boots.

00:40:48.955 --> 00:40:57.705 align:middle line:84%
Silence!

00:40:57.705 --> 00:41:00.781 align:middle line:84%
So I can't study here any longer, can I?

00:41:00.781 --> 00:41:02.972 align:middle line:84%
No.

00:41:02.972 --> 00:41:09.491 align:middle line:90%
For a minute, can I talk to Rita?
I have a gift for her.

00:41:09.491 --> 00:41:25.644 align:middle line:90%
