Or maybe, some judge?
- Out of here. Get out.

02:19:11.326 --> 02:19:16.176 align:middle line:90%
Before I leave, I'd like
to ask you a question.

02:19:16.176 --> 02:19:20.958 align:middle line:90%
What if it was your son in my place?
And because he's poor...

02:19:20.958 --> 02:19:28.237 align:middle line:90%
..because he was brought up in the slums
and was forced into crime...

02:19:28.237 --> 02:19:31.734 align:middle line:90%
...what if it was he who was being
denied his love, his life?

02:19:31.734 --> 02:19:46.417 align:middle line:84%
How would you have felt?

02:19:46.417 --> 02:19:51.415 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

02:19:51.415 --> 02:19:53.372 align:middle line:84%
Raj! Raj!

02:19:53.372 --> 02:19:56.360 align:middle line:84%
Jagga has called you.

02:19:56.360 --> 02:20:35.876 align:middle line:90%
There's a big heist.
A bank is to be looted.

02:20:35.876 --> 02:20:39.649 align:middle line:84%
Open the door!

02:20:39.649 --> 02:20:42.378 align:middle line:90%
Open up.
- Who is it?

02:20:42.378 --> 02:20:45.258 align:middle line:84%
Open up!

02:20:45.258 --> 02:20:50.805 align:middle line:84%
Open the door!

02:20:50.805 --> 02:21:00.362 align:middle line:90%
Who is there?
- Open the door!

02:21:00.362 --> 02:21:03.481 align:middle line:84%
Who are you?

02:21:03.481 --> 02:21:07.378 align:middle line:84%
Don't you know me?

02:21:07.378 --> 02:21:11.151 align:middle line:84%
I'm Jagga.

02:21:11.151 --> 02:21:13.539 align:middle line:84%
Jagga!

02:21:13.539 --> 02:21:18.187 align:middle line:90%
The bandit?
- You could say so.

02:21:18.187 --> 02:21:23.775 align:middle line:90%
What do you want here?
- Silence!

02:21:23.775 --> 02:21:29.315 align:middle line:90%
The police are after me.
Where's Raj?

02:21:29.315 --> 02:21:38.488 align:middle line:90%
Get out of my house! I will do nothing
to help someone like you!

02:21:38.488 --> 02:21:45.816 align:middle line:90%
I had you once, and I let you go
Remember the day?

02:21:45.816 --> 02:21:51.615 align:middle line:90%
For twelve years, I cared for your son.
I made his life! For this day?

02:21:51.615 --> 02:21:56.540 align:middle line:90%
Made my son's life?
You forced him into crime.

02:21:56.540 --> 02:22:00.831 align:middle line:90%
Get out of my house. I don't want
your cursed shadow upon my son!

02:22:00.831 --> 02:22:03.522 align:middle line:84%
Get out! Get out of my house!

02:22:03.522 --> 02:22:10.477 align:middle line:84%
Police! Police!

02:22:10.477 --> 02:22:13.743 align:middle line:90%
Go on! Call the police!
- Police!

02:22:13.743 --> 02:22:17.470 align:middle line:90%
Let me see who saves you!
Scream!

02:22:17.470 --> 02:22:24.339 align:middle line:84%
Jagga!

02:22:24.339 --> 02:22:33.179 align:middle line:90%
Will you challenge your boss?
- You're no boss. You're Satan!

02:22:33.179 --> 02:22:45.151 align:middle line:84%
Satan!

02:22:45.151 --> 02:23:13.294 align:middle line:84%
Let's hear what you have to say now.

02:23:13.294 --> 02:23:17.288 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

02:23:17.288 --> 02:23:24.545 align:middle line:84%
Raj! No! No! Mercy!

02:23:24.545 --> 02:23:27.742 align:middle line:84%
No! Enough!

02:23:27.742 --> 02:24:03.528 align:middle line:84%
Jagga!

02:24:03.528 --> 02:24:25.150 align:middle line:90%
What have you done Raj?
- For my sins, this is atonement!

02:24:25.150 --> 02:24:43.475 align:middle line:84%
Police!

02:24:43.475 --> 02:24:53.136 align:middle line:84%
The accused may be presented.

02:24:53.136 --> 02:25:03.574 align:middle line:90%
What's the name of the accused?
- Sir, his name is Raj.

02:25:03.574 --> 02:25:10.634 align:middle line:90%
Father's name?
- Not known, sir. Maybe he has none.

02:25:10.634 --> 02:25:13.597 align:middle line:84%
Order!

02:25:13.597 --> 02:25:20.991 align:middle line:90%
Raj, you have been accused
of killing Jagga.

02:25:20.991 --> 02:25:25.661 align:middle line:90%
Do you have anything to say
in your defence?

02:25:25.661 --> 02:25:34.621 align:middle line:90%
Have you not appointed a lawyer
to defend yourself?

02:25:34.621 --> 02:25:40.403 align:middle line:90%
The case is adjourned. The government
will appoint a counsel for the defence.

02:25:40.403 --> 02:25:46.526 align:middle line:90%
I know the law. Raj killed
in self-defence. That's no crime.

02:25:46.526 --> 02:25:50.623 align:middle line:84%
Please save my Raj, somehow.

02:25:50.623 --> 02:25:54.351 align:middle line:90%
Your deposition is very important.
The whole case hinges on it.

02:25:54.351 --> 02:26:17.667 align:middle line:90%
Come to the court tomorrow.
- All right. Okay, dear.

02:26:17.667 --> 02:26:24.704 align:middle line:84%
Husband!

02:26:24.704 --> 02:26:26.837 align:middle line:84%
She is unconscious.

02:26:26.837 --> 02:26:30.351 align:middle line:84%
Move back! Move! Move!

02:26:30.351 --> 02:26:35.880 align:middle line:90%
Is she dead?
- She has been hurt on the head.

02:26:35.880 --> 02:26:45.466 align:middle line:90%
And Raj killed Jagga
to save my life.

02:26:45.466 --> 02:26:51.342 align:middle line:90%
Please sign here. This deposition
will surely save Raj.

02:26:51.342 --> 02:26:57.541 align:middle line:90%
If Raj is saved, I will be able
to die in peace.

02:26:57.541 --> 02:27:12.852 align:middle line:84%
I should be leaving now.

02:27:12.852 --> 02:27:14.682 align:middle line:84%
Mother!

02:27:14.682 --> 02:27:16.648 align:middle line:90%
My son!
- What happened to you, Ma?

02:27:16.648 --> 02:27:17.884 align:middle line:84%
My son!

02:27:17.884 --> 02:27:22.490 align:middle line:90%
That heartless judge has killed you!
What is his enmity with us?

02:27:22.490 --> 02:27:24.958 align:middle line:90%
You mustn't blame him, son.
- Why not?

02:27:24.958 --> 02:27:26.803 align:middle line:90%
He has always been tying
to make us miserable.

02:27:26.803 --> 02:27:32.359 align:middle line:84%
No son! He is your father.

02:27:32.359 --> 02:27:34.627 align:middle line:84%
My father?

02:27:34.627 --> 02:27:39.777 align:middle line:90%
What are you saying, Ma?
What has come over you?

02:27:39.777 --> 02:27:45.678 align:middle line:90%
I'm not out of my mind, son.
What I'm saying is the truth.

02:27:45.678 --> 02:27:48.591 align:middle line:90%
I could not bring myself
to tell you this until now.

02:27:48.591 --> 02:27:55.100 align:middle line:90%
But if not today, once I'm gone
who else could tell you?

02:27:55.100 --> 02:27:59.616 align:middle line:90%
This can't be, Ma!
This can never be!

02:27:59.616 --> 02:28:05.838 align:middle line:90%
This is a long story.
But I don't have the time.

02:28:05.838 --> 02:28:12.238 align:middle line:84%
Keep this. I'm leaving.

02:28:12.238 --> 02:28:16.435 align:middle line:90%
He will surely recognise you
when you show him this.

02:28:16.435 --> 02:28:21.280 align:middle line:84%
He has never forgiven me.

02:28:21.280 --> 02:28:28.293 align:middle line:84%
But he will surely forgive his son.

02:28:28.293 --> 02:28:32.361 align:middle line:90%
I won't seek mercy from the one
who tortured my mother all her life...

02:28:32.361 --> 02:28:39.206 align:middle line:90%
..the one who made her beg from door
to door. I won't have his mercy!

02:28:39.206 --> 02:28:42.162 align:middle line:84%
Ma, I won't have his mercy!

02:28:42.162 --> 02:28:48.336 align:middle line:90%
If I could see him for
once before I died...

02:28:48.336 --> 02:28:50.686 align:middle line:84%
But why would he come here.

02:28:50.686 --> 02:28:54.538 align:middle line:90%
Come.
- I'm leaving Ma.

02:28:54.538 --> 02:28:55.728 align:middle line:84%
Son!

02:28:55.728 --> 02:28:58.376 align:middle line:90%
I'll avenge you, I will.
- No!

02:28:58.376 --> 02:29:01.266 align:middle line:90%
I'll surely avenge you, I will.
- No, son!.

02:29:01.266 --> 02:29:11.265 align:middle line:84%
Son!

02:29:11.265 --> 02:29:14.368 align:middle line:84%
The Judge is here to see you.

02:29:14.368 --> 02:29:26.782 align:middle line:90%
Which Judge?
- The one whose car ran you over.

02:29:26.782 --> 02:29:31.857 align:middle line:84%
So he has come... before I'm dead.

02:29:31.857 --> 02:29:35.666 align:middle line:84%
Alas, I cannot see.

02:29:35.666 --> 02:29:41.762 align:middle line:84%
Nurse, give him my greetings.

02:29:41.762 --> 02:29:47.804 align:middle line:90%
I am ashamed about the accident.
Please forgive me.

02:29:47.804 --> 02:29:59.146 align:middle line:84%
Forgive you?

02:29:59.146 --> 02:30:40.735 align:middle line:84%
Doctor!

02:30:40.735 --> 02:30:43.319 align:middle line:84%
Mother!

02:30:43.319 --> 02:30:48.224 align:middle line:84%
You didn't die! You were killed!

02:30:48.224 --> 02:31:18.501 align:middle line:90%
That heartless judge has killed you!
To make sure that he isn't exposed!

02:31:18.501 --> 02:31:32.163 align:middle line:84%
Judge sir!

02:31:32.163 --> 02:31:34.357 align:middle line:84%
Judge sir!

02:31:34.357 --> 02:31:41.247 align:middle line:90%
Have you decided the verdict
about the case?

02:31:41.247 --> 02:31:46.950 align:middle line:90%
Case?
- Raj's case.

02:31:46.950 --> 02:31:52.444 align:middle line:90%
You are going mad!
What are you doing to yourself?

02:31:52.444 --> 02:31:56.216 align:middle line:84%
You are a mature, educated woman.

02:31:56.216 --> 02:31:59.457 align:middle line:90%
In a few days, you'll start
going to court as a lawyer.

02:31:59.457 --> 02:32:06.957 align:middle line:90%
You might even make a judge.
If you get emotional over every case...

02:32:06.957 --> 02:32:08.642 align:middle line:90%
..you will never be able to
dispense justice.

02:32:08.642 --> 02:32:16.250 align:middle line:90%
This is not a lawsuit.
It's my life!

02:32:16.250 --> 02:32:21.545 align:middle line:90%
Do you not understand as much?
- Irrespective, it won't alter the law.

02:32:21.545 --> 02:32:23.643 align:middle line:90%
Nor should you let your emotions
come in the way of justice.

02:32:23.643 --> 02:32:27.983 align:middle line:90%
Justice is all I seek.
Raj is completely innocent.

02:32:27.983 --> 02:32:30.823 align:middle line:90%
He killed Jagga tying to save
his mother.

02:32:30.823 --> 02:32:34.664 align:middle line:90%
You can read his mother's
dying declaration.

02:32:34.664 --> 02:32:37.988 align:middle line:90%
In this particular case,
Raj might merit pardon.

02:32:37.988 --> 02:32:41.960 align:middle line:90%
But his whole life is a long story
of involvement with crime and sin.

02:32:41.960 --> 02:32:47.678 align:middle line:90%
I cannot comprehend how you can
sympathise with such a person.

02:32:47.678 --> 02:32:52.543 align:middle line:84%
How can you love him?

02:32:52.543 --> 02:33:02.581 align:middle line:84%
You have studied the law.

02:33:02.581 --> 02:33:08.603 align:middle line:84%
But my heart has not read the laws.

02:33:08.603 --> 02:33:14.737 align:middle line:84%
Heart... and the laws.

02:33:14.737 --> 02:33:21.374 align:middle line:84%
The laws... and the heart.

02:33:21.374 --> 02:33:25.227 align:middle line:84%
What a strange concoction.

02:33:25.227 --> 02:33:29.433 align:middle line:84%
But you are right.

02:33:29.433 --> 02:33:33.529 align:middle line:84%
The heart heeds no laws.

02:33:33.529 --> 02:33:37.690 align:middle line:84%
No laws at all.

02:33:37.690 --> 02:33:59.963 align:middle line:84%
Not even mine.

02:33:59.963 --> 02:34:03.775 align:middle line:90%
No!
- Get out, Rita.

02:34:03.775 --> 02:34:07.490 align:middle line:90%
I'm in a murderous rage!
- Have you gone mad?

02:34:07.490 --> 02:34:11.564 align:middle line:90%
So you have escaped?
- Yes.

02:34:11.564 --> 02:34:13.194 align:middle line:84%
To settle the score with you.

02:34:13.194 --> 02:34:13.856 align:middle line:84%
Raj..

02:34:13.856 --> 02:34:21.127 align:middle line:90%
Then you will be happy to know
that your lawyer...

02:34:21.127 --> 02:34:24.635 align:middle line:90%
...had just convinced me
about your innocence.

02:34:24.635 --> 02:34:28.300 align:middle line:90%
I was inclined to let you off
tomorrow.

02:34:28.300 --> 02:34:31.743 align:middle line:84%
I want no mercy from you.

02:34:31.743 --> 02:34:34.874 align:middle line:90%
I don't want your justice,
your law, nothing!

02:34:34.874 --> 02:34:40.214 align:middle line:84%
All I want...

02:34:40.214 --> 02:34:46.337 align:middle line:90%
Lost your nerve?
You need guts to kill someone.

02:34:46.337 --> 02:34:53.341 align:middle line:90%
You should be thanking the one
who has just saved your life.

02:34:53.341 --> 02:34:56.186 align:middle line:90%
What if I were to use this very knife
to rip your heart out?

02:34:56.186 --> 02:34:59.653 align:middle line:90%
What else can the verdict
of the courts be?

02:34:59.653 --> 02:35:03.470 align:middle line:90%
Judge Raghunath was compelled to kill
a criminal to save his own life.

02:35:03.470 --> 02:35:14.739 align:middle line:90%
Have you gone out of your mind too?
- I was. For a second.

02:35:14.739 --> 02:35:21.372 align:middle line:90%
For the scum that he is,
the hangman's noose will be better.

02:35:21.372 --> 02:35:26.272 align:middle line:84%
Raj. Raj.

02:35:26.272 --> 02:35:29.639 align:middle line:90%
This is the story of
Raj's life and crimes.

02:35:29.639 --> 02:35:35.692 align:middle line:90%
Now you know why and how
he took to crime.

02:35:35.692 --> 02:35:39.562 align:middle line:90%
My Lord, the one who is guilty
is his father...

02:35:39.562 --> 02:35:43.914 align:middle line:90%
..who drove an innocent woman from
his house, and denied his own son.

02:35:43.914 --> 02:35:46.438 align:middle line:90%
He is the one who forced them
to go begging from door to door.

02:35:46.438 --> 02:35:51.165 align:middle line:90%
And in the company of criminals,
he went astray.

02:35:51.165 --> 02:35:53.933 align:middle line:84%
My Lord and members of the Jury...

02:35:53.933 --> 02:35:56.410 align:middle line:90%
..if Raj is to be punished
for his crime..

02:35:56.410 --> 02:35:58.705 align:middle line:90%
..then his father should be
punished too.

02:35:58.705 --> 02:36:03.207 align:middle line:84%
My Lord, I would like to say something.

02:36:03.207 --> 02:36:09.304 align:middle line:90%
Emotion has got the better
of the counsel for defence.

02:36:09.304 --> 02:36:12.224 align:middle line:90%
In her anxiety to save the accused,
the counsel has presented...

02:36:12.224 --> 02:36:18.218 align:middle line:90%
..an interesting story,
however incongruous it might be...

02:36:18.218 --> 02:36:23.610 align:middle line:90%
..to try and prove that
some criminal happens to be my son!

02:36:23.610 --> 02:36:28.914 align:middle line:90%
But I ask, what evidence
does the counsel have?

02:36:28.914 --> 02:36:32.183 align:middle line:90%
No evidence on earth will convince you
that Raj is your son...

02:36:32.183 --> 02:36:35.509 align:middle line:90%
..not unless you are willing
to accept him as your son.

02:36:35.509 --> 02:36:40.980 align:middle line:90%
If there be proof, it lies deep
in your heart and in Raj's eyes.

02:36:40.980 --> 02:36:45.743 align:middle line:90%
Look at him. The same eyes,
the same high brow.

02:36:45.743 --> 02:36:49.942 align:middle line:90%
He even speaks like you speak.
He's just as adamant as you are.

02:36:49.942 --> 02:36:52.571 align:middle line:90%
Are you still not willing
to accept him as your son?

02:36:52.571 --> 02:36:56.170 align:middle line:84%
Ms Rita, the law heeds no emotion.

02:36:56.170 --> 02:37:01.330 align:middle line:90%
Nor my Lord, does the heart
heed any law.

02:37:01.330 --> 02:37:06.453 align:middle line:84%
I have no more to say.

02:37:06.453 --> 02:37:19.400 align:middle line:90%
If the accused has anything to say
in his defence, he may proceed.

02:37:19.400 --> 02:37:26.734 align:middle line:90%
Yes. At last,
after being branded a murderer...

02:37:26.734 --> 02:37:30.498 align:middle line:84%
..I hold your attention.

02:37:30.498 --> 02:37:37.671 align:middle line:90%
Had I been heard earlier, perhaps
I would never have had to stand here.

02:37:37.671 --> 02:37:40.895 align:middle line:90%
Ms Rita has tried her best
to save me from being hanged.

02:37:40.895 --> 02:37:44.115 align:middle line:90%
And not only in this particular case;
in my personal life too.

02:37:44.115 --> 02:37:49.627 align:middle line:90%
In my defence, I wish to say nothing.
I am evil.

02:37:49.627 --> 02:37:51.886 align:middle line:90%
I've been a vagabond ever since
I was a child.

02:37:51.886 --> 02:37:55.341 align:middle line:84%
I'm a murderer, a criminal.

02:37:55.341 --> 02:38:00.288 align:middle line:90%
You may punish me as you please.
But sin, crime, hatred and violence...

02:38:00.288 --> 02:38:03.486 align:middle line:90%
..this vicious circle that holds
your society in a vice-grip...

02:38:03.486 --> 02:38:06.607 align:middle line:90%
..do you think it can be broken
by hanging me?

02:38:06.607 --> 02:38:09.585 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to tell you
the story of my life.

02:38:09.585 --> 02:38:17.664 align:middle line:90%
But all I want to say is, I did not
inherit crime from my parents.

02:38:17.664 --> 02:38:19.735 align:middle line:90%
From that gutter full of filth
that flows beside my shanty...

02:38:19.735 --> 02:38:26.132 align:middle line:90%
...I picked up crime. That gutter
is still flowing over.

02:38:26.132 --> 02:38:31.207 align:middle line:84%
And the virus still breeds.

02:38:31.207 --> 02:38:35.173 align:middle line:90%
And countless children who live
in those slums...

02:38:35.173 --> 02:38:37.973 align:middle line:90%
..are falling prey to the virus
every day.

02:38:37.973 --> 02:38:45.275 align:middle line:90%
Do not think of me. Those children
are the ones you must care for.

02:38:45.275 --> 02:38:48.706 align:middle line:84%
You must care for your children.

02:38:48.706 --> 02:38:53.283 align:middle line:90%
Lest come the day when...
yours...

02:38:53.283 --> 02:38:54.955 align:middle line:84%
..and yours...

02:38:54.955 --> 02:38:58.656 align:middle line:84%
..and yours...

02:38:58.656 --> 02:39:00.801 align:middle line:90%
..and your son too stands
in these docks to reiterate...

02:39:00.801 --> 02:39:05.636 align:middle line:90%
..that it's an honest father's blood
that flows in my veins.

02:39:05.636 --> 02:39:10.839 align:middle line:90%
Time was when I was an innocent boy,
just like your sons.

02:39:10.839 --> 02:39:16.865 align:middle line:90%
Like all mothers, my mother too
wove a golden dream for me.

02:39:16.865 --> 02:39:21.699 align:middle line:90%
She would say, "My son will grow up
to become a lawyer".

02:39:21.699 --> 02:39:30.207 align:middle line:90%
Then he will become a magistrate.
And then, a judge... like his father.

02:39:30.207 --> 02:39:33.702 align:middle line:90%
I know the verdict that this court
is about to give.

02:39:33.702 --> 02:39:41.614 align:middle line:90%
And I'm willing to suffer any sentence.
For my sins, this is atonement.

02:39:41.614 --> 02:39:45.595 align:middle line:90%
But I await the decision
from yet another quarter.

02:39:45.595 --> 02:39:52.439 align:middle line:90%
I want to know Judge Raghunath,
what says your heart?

02:39:52.439 --> 02:40:19.741 align:middle line:84%
What says your heart?

02:40:19.741 --> 02:41:07.762 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

02:41:07.762 --> 02:41:13.295 align:middle line:84%
Has the Judge come to see his convict?

02:41:13.295 --> 02:41:17.169 align:middle line:84%
A father...

02:41:17.169 --> 02:41:20.121 align:middle line:84%
..who is guilty.

02:41:20.121 --> 02:41:21.778 align:middle line:84%
Guilty? You?

02:41:21.778 --> 02:41:24.385 align:middle line:84%
Yes.

02:41:24.385 --> 02:41:29.417 align:middle line:90%
Tomorrow, the law might
pronounce you guilty.

02:41:29.417 --> 02:41:36.996 align:middle line:90%
But in the eyes of God,
I am the one who is guilty.

02:41:36.996 --> 02:41:39.138 align:middle line:84%
Are you weeping?

02:41:39.138 --> 02:41:45.834 align:middle line:90%
Yes, for the father who found his son,
and yet he has lost him.

02:41:45.834 --> 02:41:47.656 align:middle line:90%
For the husband who forced his wife
to become a widow.

02:41:47.656 --> 02:41:50.889 align:middle line:90%
For society, where poverty
breeds crime.

02:41:50.889 --> 02:41:52.933 align:middle line:90%
For the son who is orphaned
though his father is alive.

02:41:52.933 --> 02:41:54.823 align:middle line:90%
For the child who goes through life
looking for someone...

02:41:54.823 --> 02:41:56.651 align:middle line:84%
..who will call him "Son".

02:41:56.651 --> 02:42:00.864 align:middle line:84%
Son.

02:42:00.864 --> 02:42:06.330 align:middle line:84%
Son!

02:42:06.330 --> 02:42:40.305 align:middle line:84%
Son!

02:42:40.305 --> 02:42:45.581 align:middle line:90%
Raj, son of Judge Raghunath,
you have been proved guilty...

02:42:45.581 --> 02:42:48.994 align:middle line:90%
..of tying to assassinate
your father, Judge Raghunath.

02:42:48.994 --> 02:42:53.558 align:middle line:90%
But in the light of the strange and
unfortunate circumstances your life...

02:42:53.558 --> 02:42:57.724 align:middle line:90%
..which your counsel Ms Rita
has presented...

02:42:57.724 --> 02:43:39.772 align:middle line:90%
..you are sentenced to only three years
of rigorous imprisonment.

02:43:39.772 --> 02:43:41.526 align:middle line:84%
Crying?

02:43:41.526 --> 02:43:43.579 align:middle line:84%
You silly girl.

02:43:43.579 --> 02:43:46.474 align:middle line:84%
Silly, lawyers never cry.

02:43:46.474 --> 02:43:48.721 align:middle line:90%
At this rate, how are you
going to practice?

02:43:48.721 --> 02:43:56.677 align:middle line:90%
What use is the practice, Raj?
I wasn't able to save you.

02:43:56.677 --> 02:44:02.406 align:middle line:90%
No Rita, this penance
is very important for me.

02:44:02.406 --> 02:44:07.966 align:middle line:90%
Only after I've been through this,
will I be worthy of you.

02:44:07.966 --> 02:44:13.141 align:middle line:90%
With you beside me,
I can go through anything.

02:44:13.141 --> 02:44:16.336 align:middle line:84%
I will become an honest man.

02:44:16.336 --> 02:44:19.848 align:middle line:84%
Everyone will say I'm a good man.

02:44:19.848 --> 02:44:24.394 align:middle line:84%
I will read, I will write.

02:44:24.394 --> 02:44:28.770 align:middle line:90%
And just like Ma used to say,
first I'll become a lawyer...

02:44:28.770 --> 02:44:33.881 align:middle line:84%
..then a magistrate.

02:44:33.881 --> 02:44:37.673 align:middle line:84%
And then, a judge.

02:44:37.673 --> 02:44:45.908 align:middle line:90%
Last night I saw a judge.
And I liked him.

02:44:45.908 --> 02:44:49.181 align:middle line:84%
I'll become a judge.

02:44:49.181 --> 02:44:51.702 align:middle line:90%
You won't call me a savage anymore,
will you?

02:44:51.702 --> 02:44:59.756 align:middle line:84%
I will. You savage!

02:44:59.756 --> 02:45:02.399 align:middle line:84%
Time up.

02:45:02.399 --> 02:45:18.927 align:middle line:84%
Come on.

02:45:18.927 --> 02:45:21.376 align:middle line:84%
Keep this.

02:45:21.376 --> 02:45:25.856 align:middle line:84%
It's your gift.

02:45:25.856 --> 02:45:28.769 align:middle line:84%
Don't worry. I didn't steal it.

02:45:28.769 --> 02:45:31.386 align:middle line:84%
I just smuggled it in.

02:45:31.386 --> 02:45:45.937 align:middle line:84%
Raj.

02:45:45.937 --> 02:45:53.424 align:middle line:90%
Not your fault, Rita.
It's just the way I look.

02:45:53.424 --> 02:45:55.134 align:middle line:84%
Raj.

02:45:55.134 --> 02:45:58.105 align:middle line:84%
Raj.

02:45:58.105 --> 02:46:04.798 align:middle line:90%
Three years isn't too long, Raj.
I'll wait for you.

02:46:04.798 --> 02:46:06.590 align:middle line:84%
Rita.

02:46:06.590 --> 02:46:14.933 align:middle line:90%
I'll wait for you!
- Don't cry.

02:46:14.933 --> 02:46:23.414 align:middle line:84%
Number 308... move it.

02:46:23.414 --> 02:46:42.161 align:middle line:84%
I should be.

02:46:42.161 --> 02:46:45.733 align:middle line:90%
"I'm not flourishing,
I am not ruined."

02:46:45.733 --> 02:46:47.981 align:middle line:84%
"Still I sing happy songs."

02:46:47.981 --> 02:46:52.968 align:middle line:84%
"Still I sing happy songs."

02:46:52.968 --> 02:46:55.865 align:middle line:84%
"My heart is filled with wounds."

02:46:55.865 --> 02:47:01.118 align:middle line:84%
"But still these lively eyes smile."

02:47:01.118 --> 02:47:06.916 align:middle line:84%
"World.."

02:47:06.916 --> 02:47:18.492 align:middle line:90%
"World, I am troubled by your
sorrows or misfortunes."

02:47:18.492 --> 02:47:23.610 align:middle line:84%
"I am a vagabond."